==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metallography
<hw>Met`al*log"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>metallum</ets> metal + <ets>-graphy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧tallographie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The science or
art of metals and metal working; also, a treatise on metals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A method of transferring impressions of the grain of
wood to metallic surfaces by chemical action.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A substitute for lithography, in which metallic
plates are used instead of stone.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metalloid</ent>⟦br⟧
